"Tutorial Build Index Text" = "Build Index generates Packages, Packages.gz, Release and packages.json. Packages is the source index read by package managers, while packages.json is RepoKit's UI cache.";
"Tutorial Install Dependencies" = "Install Dependencies";
"Tutorial Install Dependencies Text" = "Install RepoKit with Sileo so dependencies are pulled automatically. Required packages are dpkg, dpkg-dev, gzip, zstd, git and openssh-client; bzip2 and xz are optional extra index compressors.";
"Tutorial SSH Key" = "SSH Key Setup";
"Tutorial SSH Key Text" = "Generate the key on device with mkdir -p /var/mobile/.ssh and ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -f /var/mobile/.ssh/id_ed25519 -C \"you@example.com\". Add id_ed25519.pub to GitHub SSH keys; never share the private key.";
"Tutorial GitHub Setup" = "GitHub Setup";
"Tutorial GitHub Setup Text" = "Create a public GitHub repository, copy the SSH remote like git@github.com:user/repo.git, fill Remote, Branch, Username and Email in Publish > GitHub Settings, then enable Pages from main and /root after the first push.";
"Tutorial Roothide Check" = "roothide Check";
"Tutorial Roothide Check Text" = "rootless success does not prove roothide. Build with THEOS_PACKAGE_SCHEME=roothide, install only on a roothide jailbreak, open the app, run repokit-helper help, create/build a test source and check CrashReporter if it exits at launch.";
"Tutorial Create Source Text" = "Open Sources, create a source, then fill name, description, author, Base URL, scheme and architecture. RepoKit creates the local repository folders automatically.";
"Tutorial Edit Deb Text" = "Edit Control and Icon changes real deb control fields, repacks the deb, then refreshes the repository metadata. Package icons are named from the Name field.";
"Tutorial GitHub Pages Text" = "After the first push, open GitHub repository Settings > Pages, choose Deploy from a branch, select main and /root, then save.";
"Tutorial GitHub Repo Text" = "Create a public GitHub repository, add /var/mobile/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub to GitHub SSH keys, then fill the SSH remote, branch, username and email.";
"Tutorial Import Deb Text" = "Import Deb copies the selected .deb into public/debs; it does not move or delete your original file. Then RepoKit rebuilds the index.";
"Tutorial Import Source Text" = "Import an existing local repository folder when you already have a public directory. RepoKit reads Packages first, or rebuilds indexes from debs when needed.";
"Tutorial Jailbreak Compatibility" = "Jailbreak Compatibility";
"Tutorial Jailbreak Compatibility Text" = "Use logical paths such as /var/mobile/RepoKit and /usr/bin/repokit-helper. RepoKit resolves real rootless and roothide paths with jbroot(), so do not use preboot paths manually.";
"Tutorial Manage Deb Packages Text" = "Use Packages to import deb files, import installed packages, edit control fields, set icons, repack debs and refresh indexes for the active source.";
"Tutorial Manage Sources Text" = "Select a source to make it active. Editing, package lists, builds, checks and GitHub pushes all target the active source; deletion moves data to trash for recovery.";
"Tutorial Project Structure" = "Project Structure";
"Tutorial Project Structure Text" = "The root Makefile aggregates RepoKitApp and repokit-helper. control stores deb metadata, layout stores package install files, packages contains build output, and logs/repos are runtime data.";
"Tutorial Publish GitHub Text" = "Configure an SSH remote such as git@github.com:user/repo.git, branch, username and email, then push. RepoKit rebuilds indexes before committing and uses /var/mobile/.ssh/id_ed25519.";
"Tutorial RepoKit Logic" = "How RepoKit Works";
"Tutorial RepoKit Logic Text" = "The UIKit app handles screens and input. repokit-helper performs file operations, deb scanning, index generation, checks and GitHub publishing.";
"Tutorial Repository Structure" = "Repository Structure";
"Tutorial Repository Structure Text" = "Each source contains repo.json, packages.json, public/debs, public/icons, Packages, Packages.gz, Release, logs and trash. public is the folder published to package managers.";
"Tutorial Sileo Text" = "After GitHub Pages is enabled, add the Base URL such as https://user.github.io/repo in Sileo or Zebra, then refresh sources.";
"Tutorial Troubleshooting Text" = "If import fails, check path and permissions under /var/mobile. If package counts look wrong, rebuild indexes. If push fails, verify Git identity, SSH remote, /var/mobile/.ssh/id_ed25519 and Pages branch.";
